{
  "number": 2909,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2909",
  "title": "connectCurrentRefinedValues should not display values min / max of connectRange",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nBUG\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nWhen we provide min / max to `RangeSlider` (aka `connectRange`) those values are displayed in `CurrentRefinedValues`(aka `connectCurrentRefinedValues`) even when the user doesn't refine.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-04-30 at 14 50 29](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6513513/39427920-e02904b8-4c85-11e8-939c-87e748f91826.png)\r\n\r\nLive version with [CodeSandbox](https://codesandbox.io/s/74w8yn6590).\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nSince those values are not \"really\" refined they should not appear.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\n\r\nIt might be interesting to leverage the new API `getWidgetState ` combine with mapper to generate the list of refinements for `connectCurrentRefinedValues` (similar to what React InstantSearch does).\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n\r\n2.7.1\r\n",
